{
  "stem": "1895.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 284.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And [BACKGROUND NOISE] somehow we embraced, because we knew-- somehow I feel that, in his face and in my face, the tragedy of the Jews that was happening to us was reflected.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he asked me what's going on, if I know what's happening.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I told him what I knew.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I knew then that my family was still safe, because he didn't know anything, and nothing had happened in that part of town yet.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I left him there, and I ran upstairs.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We lived two flights up, on the second floor.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I opened the door, and I found my father, and my mother, and my sister Bluma.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They were all-- They were all dressed, ready to go, with a few bundles near the door.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You know, couple of valises with backpack.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they were just sitting there waiting until the Germans come and they say, [SPEAKING GERMAN] which was-- that was the-- that was the call.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And when I opened the door, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] [SIGHS] they looked at me, and they couldn't believe it, that I made it back home.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I told them at the time what I had seen.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Not what I had seen on the field, but what I had seen once I came back to the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I didn't want to disturb them with that.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "As young as I was, I knew I shouldn't do that.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I told them that it was all over, that they're not going to take for resettlement any more people that day, because they had filled the quota.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And strangely, my father went out and he told the neighbors the good news.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
